### Recursive Fence

Generate posts.

```scheme
(define (posts x n)
  (if (zero? n)
      '()
      (cons (entity 'rect (at x 200) (width 10) (height 70) (fill 'brown))
            (posts (+ x 35) (- n 1)))))

(define (frame t)
  (apply world
         (cons (background 'skyblue)
               (posts 60 10))))

(render-at 0.0)
```

[VISUAL: Ten fence posts spaced evenly across the frame.]

`posts` recurses to build a list; `apply world` spreads it.

---


### Varying Heights

Posts of different lengths.

```scheme
(define (posts-varied x heights)
  (if (null? heights)
      '()
      (cons (entity 'rect
                    (at x 200)
                    (width 10)
                    (height (car heights))
                    (fill 'sienna))
            (posts-varied (+ x 30) (cdr heights)))))

(define (frame t)
  (apply world
         (cons (background 'lightyellow)
               (posts-varied 80 '(60 70 65 80 75 70 85)))))

(render-at 0.0)
```

[VISUAL: Seven fence posts with varying heights creating an irregular skyline.]

We pass a list of heights and `car` / `cdr` through it.

