### Depth of Field (Via Blur Proxy)

<!-- BUILD: blur filter or depth-of-field shader -->

*[needs: blur or depth-of-field rendering]*

In a real engine, we'd apply a blur filter to background entities. For now, we approximate with opacity and color softness:

```scheme
(define (frame t)
  (world
    (background 'white)
    ; far (soft)
    (entity 'circle (at 120 150) (radius 50) (fill 'lightgray) (opacity 0.4))
    ; mid
    (entity 'circle (at 200 150) (radius 50) (fill 'gray) (opacity 0.7))
    ; near (sharp)
    (entity 'circle (at 280 150) (radius 50) (fill 'black) (opacity 1.0))))

(render-at 0.0)
```

[VISUAL: Three circles — the left one faint, the middle one mid-tone, the right one sharp and dark.]

Opacity and color intensity stand in for focus depth until true blur is wired.

